WEBVTT

00:21.980 --> 00:24.691
If they know we've infiltrated,
then why aren't there any Doshi?

00:25.942 --> 00:27.193
Is it a trap?

00:29.029 --> 00:30.238
Or is it...

00:32.115 --> 00:33.825
The final destination is the water gate.

00:34.617 --> 00:36.327
From there, we leave the island by boat.

00:36.911 --> 00:39.039
The water gate is at the very back
of the inner citadel,

00:39.122 --> 00:40.832
beneath the main palace.

00:40.915 --> 00:44.002
The elixir retrieval team
and the escape route team

00:44.085 --> 00:45.503
will rendezvous here.

00:45.587 --> 00:48.047
Are we waiting for everyone to gather?

00:48.131 --> 00:51.634
No way! As soon
as the elixir arrives, we get out.

00:51.718 --> 00:54.137
Anyone too slow gets left behind.

00:54.220 --> 00:56.556
It’s not that simple.

00:56.639 --> 00:59.893
Even a medium Tang ship
needs five people to operate.

00:59.976 --> 01:04.022
It may sound harsh,
but at least five must make it.

01:04.105 --> 01:05.940
Otherwise, escape won’t even be possible.

01:08.860 --> 01:10.820
Five of us have to survive.

01:16.993 --> 01:17.911
This is...

01:17.994 --> 01:22.082
The more you regenerate,
the more your body turns to tree.

01:22.165 --> 01:26.419
If it keeps spreading, death,
or, maybe an even worse, hell awaits.

01:31.758 --> 01:35.929
Yui... If she saw my body now,
she'd be pretty shocked.

01:37.138 --> 01:40.934
I want to see... that shocked face... of hers.

03:22.368 --> 03:23.536
That's the angle!

03:24.203 --> 03:27.373
It was tough shaving down the guard,
but it turned out great!

03:27.457 --> 03:28.875
Eyepatch!

03:28.958 --> 03:31.044
Look, Toma! Look!

03:33.796 --> 03:37.550
Wouldn’t it look cooler
if the stem part were straight?

03:37.634 --> 03:40.929
No, no, it's cooler diagonal!

03:41.012 --> 03:42.180
Right, Gantetsusai?

03:42.263 --> 03:44.599
I want to look like a master.

03:44.682 --> 03:47.060
I don’t want something flashy
and obviously cool.

03:47.143 --> 03:48.937
I want that master aura.

03:49.687 --> 03:52.690
One look at me and you'll think
I'm some hermit old man.

03:52.774 --> 03:56.527
And since there’s no mirror,
I have no idea about "this angle".

03:56.611 --> 03:58.196
He says so himself.

03:58.905 --> 04:01.950
You all have taste as terrible
as your physical conditions.

04:02.867 --> 04:04.827
You’re pretty blunt.

04:08.539 --> 04:11.626
If you don’t get dressed soon,
you'll catch a cold, old man.

04:11.709 --> 04:14.087
It hasn't dried at all yet.

04:14.170 --> 04:15.463
Idiots.

04:15.546 --> 04:17.840
Do you really have time to fool around?

04:18.424 --> 04:20.343
We’re just getting ready.

04:20.426 --> 04:22.971
- Don’t talk back to my brother.
- You're already dressed?!

04:23.054 --> 04:25.556
I don’t know the details,

04:25.640 --> 04:28.726
but the leader of those Tensen
is plotting something.

04:31.521 --> 04:34.983
Deep inside the main palace,
there’s a monster called Pangu.

04:35.066 --> 04:39.529
They’re planning to use it to turn all
the people on the mainland into elixir.

04:39.612 --> 04:41.864
I don’t know what comes after that.

04:41.948 --> 04:44.117
But this battle

04:44.200 --> 04:46.077
is just a stalling tactic.

04:47.662 --> 04:50.873
You call it the "Rite of Abstaining
and Sustaining Life," right?

04:50.957 --> 04:54.669
What if the Tensen die during that ritual?

04:54.752 --> 04:55.628
They’re your own people.

04:59.590 --> 05:00.633
They won’t die.

05:00.717 --> 05:03.761
Even if they do, it won’t matter.

05:06.222 --> 05:08.766
Shut up! Don’t talk so complicated!

05:08.850 --> 05:10.393
It’s not complicated.

05:10.476 --> 05:14.605
And about the eyepatch, the angle
the short guy mentioned looks cooler.

05:17.817 --> 05:20.862
What were you doing
on the Tensen side, Brother?

05:20.945 --> 05:25.408
Huh? Oh, practicing bedchamber arts
and getting dissected, over and over.

05:27.035 --> 05:29.662
Anyway, our objective hasn't changed.

05:29.746 --> 05:32.290
We go to the water gate and secure a ship.

05:32.373 --> 05:36.294
If we take a ship, we might
be able to stop Rien’s plan too.

05:36.878 --> 05:39.797
Aza Chobe, will you come with us?

05:43.551 --> 05:44.427
I...

05:51.476 --> 05:52.935
What was that?

05:54.353 --> 05:56.856
Is your body... okay?

05:57.523 --> 06:00.735
Any injuries? Should we walk a bit slower?

06:02.403 --> 06:03.446
Any dizziness?

06:03.529 --> 06:07.033
Hey, those are all my lines, Sensei.

06:09.327 --> 06:11.079
I see, you're right.

06:11.162 --> 06:13.122
You’re such a worrier.

06:13.206 --> 06:15.583
I'm just a criminal
with my executioner, aren't I?

06:22.173 --> 06:25.843
We’ll wait to regroup with the others
beneath the main palace.

06:26.427 --> 06:29.222
But worst case, even if we can't regroup,

06:30.056 --> 06:31.349
and even without the elixer,

06:32.183 --> 06:34.685
I intend to get you back to the mainland.

06:35.645 --> 06:37.605
What do you mean by that?

06:38.231 --> 06:41.359
Don’t worry.
I’ll stay with you to the very end.

06:41.984 --> 06:45.446
Instead of returning to Edo, let’s travel
the mountains of the provinces together.

06:46.030 --> 06:47.240
Even under Tokugawa rule,

06:47.865 --> 06:51.119
some domains must still have lands
where mountain folk live.

06:51.202 --> 06:55.540
You might find a way of life that
suits you better than hiding in a town.

06:59.460 --> 07:02.713
Until then, I’ll protect you.
I’ve decided that.

07:03.881 --> 07:05.508
As long as there’s light in my eyes.

07:07.135 --> 07:08.010
Huh?

07:09.720 --> 07:12.515
Does that mean your eye color changes?

07:12.598 --> 07:14.642
No, that's not what I meant.

07:15.268 --> 07:17.687
You had your eyes open while fighting.

07:18.312 --> 07:19.480
Do they actually change color?

07:19.564 --> 07:20.648
Ah, no.

07:20.731 --> 07:22.483
It’s just an expression.

07:22.567 --> 07:23.609
Tao?

07:23.693 --> 07:25.111
It has nothing to do with Tao.

07:28.406 --> 07:29.991
What’s that?

07:30.074 --> 07:31.159
A rumble...

07:39.417 --> 07:41.252
It’s gone quiet.

07:41.335 --> 07:43.796
It was massive, but distant.

07:44.964 --> 07:46.048
I don't sense any presence either.

07:55.475 --> 08:00.229
Criminals will be executed on the spot.

08:01.147 --> 08:06.235
We have been granted discretion
by Shugen of the Yamada Asaemon.

08:07.028 --> 08:08.738
Likewise, anyone who shelters criminals,

08:09.489 --> 08:11.491
anyone who stains the Asaemon name...

08:15.578 --> 08:17.205
We will take your life.

08:27.256 --> 08:29.258
Iwagakure’s new face.

08:39.352 --> 08:40.436
So you've come...

08:42.355 --> 08:43.523
Gabimaru.

08:45.733 --> 08:49.862
Behead anyone who is not
Yamada Asaemon on site!

08:49.946 --> 08:51.656
Execution by proxy is authorized.

08:51.739 --> 08:53.115
We’re moving too!

08:53.199 --> 08:54.408
- Yes, sir!
- Aye!

08:57.078 --> 09:00.915
It’s something different from youth.

09:00.998 --> 09:04.919
Well then, I think I’ll serve
as the rear guard here.

09:06.003 --> 09:08.589
Hm? Your eyes doubt me.

09:08.673 --> 09:10.675
Think I’m just lying
because I want to slack off?

09:10.758 --> 09:14.428
You’re liars too, aren’t you?

09:14.512 --> 09:16.556
Pretending to obey the shogunate.

09:16.639 --> 09:18.933
I don’t know what you’re plotting.

09:21.519 --> 09:25.064
The name "Gabimaru"
is the symbol of Iwagakure.

09:25.147 --> 09:30.486
Kill the traitor, Shija,
no, the next Gabimaru.

09:30.570 --> 09:33.781
Kill your predecessor
and become the new Gabimaru.

09:33.864 --> 09:37.451
Return the symbol of fear to the village.

09:37.535 --> 09:41.080
Rest assured, you clever samurai.

09:41.163 --> 09:44.584
Our objective is largely the same.

09:44.667 --> 09:46.711
Oh? I see.

09:46.794 --> 09:50.965
As ordered by Shugen,
we will not harm members

09:51.048 --> 09:53.467
of the Yamada school unless
they are traitors.

09:53.551 --> 09:55.595
We will protect them.

09:55.678 --> 09:57.346
Our goal is...

09:58.472 --> 10:01.100
to kill everyone else.

10:01.684 --> 10:05.229
Kill... everyone who stains the Yamada name.

10:05.313 --> 10:09.358
Kill... everyone who obstructs Shugen.

10:09.442 --> 10:13.237
Kill... everyone
who does not fear the village.

10:13.321 --> 10:17.366
Kill... everyone who knows the truth.

10:17.450 --> 10:21.495
Kill, kill, kill them all.

10:25.875 --> 10:29.211
Yeah, I guess we don’t
get along after all.

10:29.295 --> 10:31.505
Well, do your best.

10:32.214 --> 10:36.469
To tell the truth,
I feel the same, clever samurai.

10:36.552 --> 10:39.013
Killing is secondary.

10:39.972 --> 10:44.518
I came to bring that person back. Because...

10:49.815 --> 10:51.317
ever since then...

10:52.610 --> 10:54.987
you're the only one I've ever...

11:00.618 --> 11:01.994
This is...

11:02.078 --> 11:03.204
Hurry!

11:04.580 --> 11:07.875
Rien. The Tensen have all been defeated.

11:07.958 --> 11:10.586
The Rite of Abstaining and Sustaining Life
has failed.

11:10.670 --> 11:12.129
Humans are coming.

11:12.213 --> 11:13.506
We must act.

11:13.589 --> 11:15.966
There’s someone skilled at infiltration.

11:16.050 --> 11:19.261
They’re far too fast... beyond expectations.

11:21.222 --> 11:22.515
It can’t be helped.

11:22.598 --> 11:24.767
Leave the minimum personnel here.

11:24.850 --> 11:27.603
All other Doshi, prepare to intercept.

11:27.686 --> 11:30.106
Artillery and fortress weapons
won’t make it in time.

11:30.189 --> 11:34.777
Quartermaster, ready the cavalry
and rapid response units.

11:35.861 --> 11:37.321
It's all-out war.

11:37.947 --> 11:40.074
Don’t worry about
the situation of the battle or losses.

11:41.409 --> 11:44.954
As long as we buy time, that’s enough.

11:45.037 --> 11:48.916
Soon, everything will return to normal.

11:50.459 --> 11:51.585
Let’s go.

12:10.146 --> 12:11.564
Out of my way!

12:19.363 --> 12:20.239
Nurugai!

12:32.001 --> 12:34.503
Nurugai! Break through them
and head to the water gate!

12:35.880 --> 12:38.924
Sensei, this way! I can see in the dark!

12:39.008 --> 12:40.509
Huh? You can?

12:41.760 --> 12:42.720
All right!

12:42.803 --> 12:45.473
I’m not joking!

12:45.556 --> 12:48.225
You think I'd get taken down
by small fry at this point?!

12:49.101 --> 12:51.228
Don’t engage every single one!

12:51.312 --> 12:53.105
This is basically a full-scale battle now!

12:53.189 --> 12:54.565
I know!

12:54.648 --> 12:56.609
You thieving brothers! You run too!

12:57.735 --> 12:59.111
Don’t give my brother orders!

12:59.195 --> 13:02.948
In all this chaos,
he’s planning to leave the island.

13:07.745 --> 13:09.622
I know war.

13:09.705 --> 13:12.374
War isn’t the same as fighting.

13:13.250 --> 13:15.794
It goes far beyond a test of strength.

13:15.878 --> 13:18.631
Whether you live or die becomes pure luck.

13:18.714 --> 13:22.051
It’s not interesting,
and it’s nothing to be proud of.

13:22.134 --> 13:24.386
War is just shit.

13:24.470 --> 13:27.389
The ones who survive war
are the ones who run,

13:27.473 --> 13:29.767
or the ones who make
their subordinates fight,

13:30.601 --> 13:32.853
or inhuman demons...

13:35.731 --> 13:39.527
Shugen, the cavalry... Shugen!

13:40.402 --> 13:41.487
Eizen-dono...

13:42.613 --> 13:43.697
Everyone!

14:23.070 --> 14:25.072
Don’t just aim for the head,
aim for the navel too!

14:25.739 --> 14:27.825
That’s... incredible!

14:27.908 --> 14:30.244
Have you experienced war before?

14:31.328 --> 14:33.998
This isn’t war. It’s execution!

14:34.623 --> 14:38.002
A purge of rebels who raised their hands
against the shogunate’s executioners.

14:38.085 --> 14:40.754
Seal off their escape
and slaughter them all!

14:44.592 --> 14:46.719
I didn’t sense any presence.

14:47.761 --> 14:48.762
Who are you?

14:48.846 --> 14:52.391
That’s quite a fleet.
What were you planning?

14:53.350 --> 14:55.895
I have no intention of dealing with you.

14:55.978 --> 14:58.898
But if I wait here, that person will...

14:58.981 --> 15:00.482
Are you...

15:00.566 --> 15:02.359
what they call ninja in Japan?

15:02.443 --> 15:05.321
Well, whatever. Kill them.

15:11.785 --> 15:14.204
Want to see ninjutsu?

15:21.962 --> 15:24.298
Ninpo: Hiboshi.

15:27.259 --> 15:30.054
Leave one ship. Burn the rest.

15:30.137 --> 15:32.806
This one... I’ll handle.

15:55.037 --> 15:58.999
I can see it. The opponent’s Tao,
the flow of their movements.

15:59.792 --> 16:02.252
Compared to a Tensen, I have a chance.

16:06.340 --> 16:09.259
Ninjas and Doshi. And us.

16:09.343 --> 16:12.262
It looks like a three-way battle,
but the Doshi aren’t attacking Mei.

16:12.346 --> 16:14.765
The shinobi aren’t attacking me either.

16:15.599 --> 16:17.768
They must have strict orders
from their respective masters.

16:18.727 --> 16:20.854
If we exploit that gap,
we can break through!

16:25.192 --> 16:26.318
A horse?

16:48.465 --> 16:49.341
Hey.

16:49.925 --> 16:51.218
Yuzuriha!

16:51.301 --> 16:53.846
Yeah, I was going to change clothes,

16:53.929 --> 16:56.598
but Ran’s palace only had Taoist robes.

16:56.682 --> 16:58.851
I got delayed looking around.

17:00.060 --> 17:03.564
Actually, I was just waiting to recover.

17:04.898 --> 17:05.816
Did you miss me?

17:05.899 --> 17:07.317
Yes!

17:11.780 --> 17:13.282
Yu... Yuzuriha!

17:13.365 --> 17:15.325
You have to make sure they're dead.

17:15.409 --> 17:17.619
But they’re the shogunate's...

17:17.703 --> 17:19.038
Oh, sweetie!

17:19.121 --> 17:22.833
Unlike Gabi, you’re so soft, Sagirin.

17:22.916 --> 17:23.792
It’s not good, though.

17:23.876 --> 17:26.003
I checked along the way.

17:26.086 --> 17:28.047
The situation is absolutely terrible.

17:28.797 --> 17:31.300
Armed Iwagakure shinobi and the Doshi

17:31.383 --> 17:33.761
came from the direction of the water gate.

17:33.844 --> 17:35.804
They’ve probably got the exit too.

17:35.888 --> 17:39.808
It’s war all over the place.

17:39.892 --> 17:41.685
That can’t be...

17:41.769 --> 17:43.187
If they’re reinforcements
from the shogunate,

17:43.270 --> 17:45.272
maybe we can persuade them...

17:45.355 --> 17:48.317
Sweetie, not with their intent to kill.

17:48.400 --> 17:50.694
At the very least,
criminals get no negotiation.

17:51.361 --> 17:54.823
That won’t work...
We all have to make it back together.

17:54.907 --> 17:56.700
Oh, you're such a sweetie!

17:57.743 --> 17:59.495
That’s what I like about you.

17:59.578 --> 18:01.705
But what we have to do hasn’t changed.

18:02.498 --> 18:05.793
Everyone just fulfills their original
objective as fast as possible.

18:06.418 --> 18:09.129
That’s the best option. It’s the only one.

18:09.213 --> 18:10.923
Which path leads to the main palace?

18:11.006 --> 18:14.134
It would be more efficient
to split up and search.

18:14.760 --> 18:18.680
True, the elixir also seems
to be at the water gate now.

18:19.765 --> 18:22.559
If the objectives are all in one place,
that makes things simpler.

18:26.522 --> 18:27.940
But...

18:28.565 --> 18:32.194
Mei, will you come with us
and try to persuade Rien?

18:35.072 --> 18:36.240
Sagiri!

18:41.703 --> 18:43.372
Isuzu...

18:43.455 --> 18:44.998
Thank goodness...

18:45.958 --> 18:48.710
You’re alive, Sagiri...

18:48.794 --> 18:49.711
Huh?

18:51.547 --> 18:54.383
Is that Yuzuriha of Keishu?

18:55.342 --> 18:58.011
Did you kill the ninjas? The two of you?

18:58.095 --> 19:01.598
N-no, it’s just... there are circumstances.

19:02.182 --> 19:05.185
Given the situation, we’ve ended up
working together with criminals.

19:07.437 --> 19:09.731
Yuzuriha of Keishu.

19:09.815 --> 19:12.776
Guilty of infiltrating Sagiwa Castle
and murder

19:12.860 --> 19:16.238
and many other crimes.
A death sentence has been declared.

19:16.321 --> 19:19.199
There are many people
whose lives she’s taken.

19:20.576 --> 19:23.328
Those she killed, and their families.

19:24.913 --> 19:27.708
Don’t be misled, Sagiri.

19:27.791 --> 19:29.543
She’s a villain.

19:30.335 --> 19:33.463
Nuru... gai? What a strange name.

19:33.547 --> 19:38.260
"Defiant tribes...
rebelling against pacification..."

19:38.343 --> 19:41.346
"Disturbing the order of a peaceful age..."

19:42.014 --> 19:43.599
Uh?

19:44.391 --> 19:48.854
So basically a villain
who defied the shogun, right?

19:48.937 --> 19:52.608
"Aza Chobe of Iyo, great criminal."

19:52.691 --> 19:56.862
"Murder, robbery, assault, extortion..."

19:57.738 --> 20:01.491
Ugh, what a hassle.
That’s impressive, young man.

20:01.575 --> 20:05.704
You could be executed
a hundred times over. Quite the villain.

20:06.663 --> 20:08.874
By the way, Toma?

20:08.957 --> 20:11.752
I’ve been wondering since you joined.

20:12.419 --> 20:16.757
Are you, perhaps... that? Are you?

20:16.840 --> 20:20.510
We’ve decided to punish
not only criminals.

20:20.594 --> 20:22.512
For the sake of the Asaemon who've died...

20:23.972 --> 20:25.807
For his honor...

20:25.891 --> 20:28.185
The island’s monsters...

20:28.268 --> 20:30.812
And those who shelter them...

20:30.896 --> 20:33.815
Even if that someone is an Asaemon.

20:34.608 --> 20:38.612
So please, Sagiri. Leave her.

20:38.695 --> 20:40.447
Come over here.

20:43.450 --> 20:46.954
Once we get a clear path,
we’ll go back for the brothers.

20:47.537 --> 20:50.958
You’re so dutiful. Let’s just ditch them.

20:51.541 --> 20:54.044
No. We're going back for them.

20:55.671 --> 20:57.297
You’re Tamiya Gantetsusai, right?

21:00.175 --> 21:04.846
Disrespect toward a daimyo,
assault in various regions...

21:05.555 --> 21:08.809
A vicious criminal who's committed
countless major crimes.

21:11.603 --> 21:13.105
Goosebumps?

21:18.068 --> 21:19.361
Shuu-kun.

22:06.658 --> 22:09.870
No matter what hardships await...

22:12.956 --> 22:15.876
No matter how bloodstained
the road may be...

22:15.959 --> 22:19.504
For you, I will return alive.

22:50.118 --> 22:52.079
No matter what hell I face.

24:23.545 --> 24:25.839
Subtitle translation by: Maslin Friedman
